# Parameterization Schema

JSON Schema for PhenoKits parameterizable configurations.

## Overview

Configs in `configs/` support parameterization via `{{VARIABLE}}` syntax.
Parameters are validated against these schemas before use.

## Parameter Types

### Required Parameters
Must be provided by the consuming project:
- `{{PROJECT_NAME}}` - Project identifier
- `{{ORG_NAME}}` - Organization name
- `{{GITHUB_REPO}}` - GitHub repository path

### Optional Parameters
Have defaults, can be overridden:
- `{{RUST_VERSION}}` - Rust version (default: 1.75)
- `{{NODE_VERSION}}` - Node version (default: 20)
- `{{GOLANG_VERSION}}` - Go version (default: 1.22)
- `{{LOG_LEVEL}}` - Log level (default: info)
- `{{ENVIRONMENT}}` - Environment (default: development)

### Secret Parameters
Must come from secret manager:
- `{{SECRET:NAME}}` - Reference to secret
- `{{API_KEY:PROVIDER}}` - API key reference
- `{{DB_PASSWORD}}` - Database password

## Schema Files

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "project": {
      "type": "object",
      "required": ["name", "org"],
      "properties": {
        "name": {
          "type": "string",
          "pattern": "^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*$"
        },
        "org": {
          "type": "string",
          "pattern": "^[A-Z][a-zA-Z]+$"
        }
      }
    },
    "runtime": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "rust": { "type": "string", "default": "1.75" },
        "node": { "type": "string", "default": "20" },
        "go": { "type": "string", "default": "1.22" },
        "python": { "type": "string", "default": "3.12" }
      }
    },
    "secrets": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "string",
        "pattern": "^SECRET:[A-Z_]+$"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Usage

```bash
# Validate a parameterized config
pheno-kits validate --config configs/tooling/ruff.toml

# Apply parameters
pheno-kits apply --config configs/cicd/ci.yml \
  --vars project.name=myapp,org=MyOrg
```
